1 unit Tofu
2 unit Sandwich Bun
113 g Green Cabbage, shredded
1 unit Mini Cucumber
7 g Dill
4 tbsp BBQ Sauce
2 tbsp Garlic Spread
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
1 tbsp BBQ Seasoning
½ tbsp White Wine Vinegar
1 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
Meanwhile, pat tofu dry with paper towels. Cut tofu in half parallel to the cutting board. (NOTE: You will have two square tofu steaks per block.) Using a fork, poke tofu all over. Season with salt, pepper and BBQ Seasoning.

When the pan is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then tofu. Sear until golden-brown, 1-2 min per side.
Remove from heat, then transfer tofu to prepared baking sheet.
Bake in the middle of the oven until tender and golden, 6-8 min.

Meanwhile, thinly slice cucumber.
Using kitchen shears, snip as much dill as desired into a large bowl.
Add mayo, half the vinegar (use all for 4 ppl) and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar to the same bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.
Add cabbage and cucumbers, then toss to coat.

Halve buns.
Add garlic spread to cut sides.
Arrange directly on the top rack of the oven, cut-side up.
Toast until golden-brown, 3-4 min. (TIP: Keep an eye on them so they don't burn!)

Add BBQ sauce to a microwavable bowl or a small pan. Microwave until warmed through, 30 sec. (TIP: You can skip this step if you don't want to warm the BBQ sauce.)

Thinly slice tofu.
Divide tofu, slaw and toasts between plates.
Drizzle BBQ sauce over tofu.